document_title: Dangerous neurological diseases: Causes and symptoms
subsection_content:
There are many different symptoms that show that the condition of the nervous system is developing abnormally. The most common signs include:
Muscle pain and weakness;; Frequent headaches;; Blurred vision;; Convulsion;; Cognitive impairment;; Numbness in hands and feet, difficulty moving;; Stutter;; Memory is affected, deterioration;; Personality changes; And there are many other symptoms…
